[[tab Writing guide]]
[[div class="darkdocument"]]
+ So you want to write something to Hunter Industries?

Hunter Industries is an organization that [[*user EvilAngel413]] came up with in 2018, during this time this idea has evolved, disappeared and appeared again. Until it finally appeared on the website in its current form. The organization deals with the creation of weapons, technology, and vehicles using mainly demons as either a power source or literal parts of their products. When writing the Hunter Industries format, think about how you want to sell the product you are writing about. Do not list its flaws, or at least do not underline them. In official leaflets that are intended for customers, your product is perfect, created especially for them and they will not be able to live without it. **They must have it.** Also quite important, Hunter Industries in worlds where demons or anomalies are not common knowledge will not call demons by name in their leaflets. See [[[http://scp-int.wikidot.com/zlecenie-mef-2839|Order MEF-2839]]] where the word "demon" does not appear once in the leaflet. EZAW is referred to as "green, clean energy" and the demons are called "suppliers". In [[[projekt-aplikacji-malphas|App project - Malphas]]], for example, also in the leaflet the word "demon" is not mentioned, "voluntary host" is used. As you can see, in both of these formats, the workers are talking to each other about demons, openly, without beating around the bush. They know perfectly well what they are doing. It is in universes where knowledge of demons and anomalies is non-public, what about others? For example, in [[[krolewska-fundacya-hub|Royal Foundation]]], the Hunter's Forge will talk directly about the fact that it creates its products from chortas, and in [[[lady-poludnia|Southernmost Lands]]] the Hunter Armorers' Guild will not pretend that demons do not exist. Additionally, the product names themselves from Hunter Industries often refer either to the names of demons or pagan deities.

What is also worth remembering when writing about Hunter Industries, they try to protect themselves from every possible angle. They sign contracts with intelligent demons they intend to use. Do they keep these contracts once they have the demon at home? This is a different story. Potential problems from the Foundation? [[[http://scp-int.wikidot.com/scp-pl-289|Manipulate Foundation into signing a blood pact with them.]]]

+ Relationships with other organizations

* **[[[http://scp-int.wikidot.com/argus-inc-hub|A.R.G.U.S. Inc.]]]** -- Hunter Industries collaborates with A.R.G.U.S. Inc. on a variable customer/seller basis; A.R.G.U.S. in return for the supplies of equipment, offer their military personnel to guard the Hunter Industries facilities, where ordinary security cannot.
* **[[[marshall-carter-and-dark-hub|Marshall, Carter & Dark]]]** -- The relationship between MC&D and Hunter Industries remains purely business, with MC&D sometimes purchasing equipment to increase its protection or to broker trade.
* **[[[http://scp-int.wikidot.com/raptor-tec-industries|Raptor Tec Industries]]]** -- At the beginning of Hunter Industries existence, Raptor Tec was an extremely strong competitor on the European market, however, with the destruction of their only site, the competition turned into a kind of cooperation.
* **[[[goc-hub-page|Global Occult Coalition]]]** -- As the part of the name "Occult" suggests, GOC is not afraid to use tools of slightly darker origin. This is not very common, but sometimes the organization buys equipment from Hunter Industries and then uses it for its own purposes. The relationship of both of these organizations is purely business.


